author: John Varlas
title: Week 9 prep football roundup
text:
Related Coverage Northpoint improves to 9-0; Central edges past Southwind (3) MUS 31, Briarcrest 12: University of Memphis commitment Thomas Pickens scored three touchdowns as the Owls (6-2, 2-0 Division 2-AA West) clinched a first-round playoff bye. Pickens caught a 17-yard pass from Steven Regis and scored on runs of 1 and 3 yards. Rashad Muhammad and Charles Elliot had TD runs for the Saints (4-4, 0-2).
(5) CBHS 49, MUS 13: The Brothers (6-2, 2-0 Division 2-AA West) also wrapped up a first-round bye as Austin Lee ran for 239 yards on 18 carries and scored on runs of 4, 7 and 19 yards.
(10) St. George's 73, Tipton-Rosemark 7: The Gryphons (7-1, 3-0 Division 2-A West) had 43 points at the end of the first quarter and 71 at halftime against the Rebels (1-6, 0-3). Chase Hayden scored on runs of 48, 20, 10 and 88 yards and caught a 30-yard touchdown pass from Ben Glass.
Brighton 37, Wooddale 34: Brighton, winner of three games in 2014, improved to 7-1 and 4-1 in Region 8-5A. Chase Kidd threw scoring passes of 20 yards to Austin Kelley and 11 yards to Aaron Alston, who also scored on a 50-yard run. Wooddale quarterback Jerry Craine passed for 294 yards and three touchdowns to move within 466 yards of Kenton Evans' regular-season record of 3,055 with two games left.
Carver 58, BTW 20: Anthony Foster ran for two touchdowns and passed for two more as the Cobras (8-1, 6-0 Region 8-1A) won their eighth game in a row. Foster's scoring runs covered 12 and 34 yards while connecting with Roderious Sanders on 27 and 31-yard touchdowns. BTW falls to 0-8 and 0-4.
KIPP 54, Middleton 6: The Phoenix (6-2, 2-1 Region 8-1A) closed in on a playoff berth as Telly Crawford returned interceptions 56 and 50 yards in a 38-point second quarter. Eric Thomas scored on a 3-yard run and a 42-yard punt return while Dewayne Betts threw three touchdown passes, 25 yards to Ladarious Salton and 29 and 55 to Orreon Finley.
Lausanne 17, ECS 7: The Lynx (4-3, 1-2 Division 2-A) improved their playoff hopes, holding the Eagles (2-6, 1-2) to minus-15 yards on the ground. Chris Witherspoon ran for 149 yards and a touchdown and Mario Nolan-Dillard scored on a 26-yard run. ECS' points came on a 57-yard pass from Keegan Westbrook to Sumner Darlington.
